headline: Value-Investing Winner Bets Big on Out-of-Favor Energy Stocks. Think Conoco, APA.
summary: The Smead Value Fund, which has beaten the Russell 1000 Value Index over five, 10, and 15 years, has 21% of its assets in energy. The weighting in the S&P 500 is 3%.
